content: Welcome to the Online Renju Class analysis lesson!
I am Istvan Virag, This is my second teaching in the Analysis Department. I am very glad to teach here.
Now, we are ready to begin. Today we will revise some games from 5th ORC Championship tournament.
we know you can do a good lesson!
Of course, we congratulate to Renju_Liu_t, he won the championship. It was great job!
You can see in many times in offline tournaments that some games have absolutly identical move sequence.
a lot, seems like ppl learn moves by heart
I looked at some games people talked about in forum
Another question, Who have played monkey games already?
I don't know what it is
Monkey games means: moves are same on 2 or more boards
Not only move sequence same in these games, but the progress is same.
What means that progress is same?
It means that both (or more) board have same number of stones from beginning to end in all time.
one person plays black and white ?
hehe, torsten, i played "monkey" chess like that lont time ago

Yes Torsten. There is another type of "monkey game" where same player plays two identical game but different colors. Then this player get at least 1-0 or 0-1 or 1/2-1/2 on both boards. But st is unfair morals!!!
yes, two games in the same time, one white one black
The player connect two strong players, hehe
and pass the white moves to the black player and viceversa
But today we speak about "fair monkey games"
Where one player have some identical games with same color! Ok?
as a simultaneos game against more opponents?
Ok, but how does it happen? Isn't it quite unlikely?

yzhnie, casar, Torsten, puma2005, endlessroad, sirasoni, Timo, Joe1980cn, hobbang, slamduk, xfeifeix, Tear, iris, Liuchao, Tornado, Phfay, voshkod, tommy, dudu, yboil, konjin, xuwu, HOT, sosei, weigui, shuwang, ouyang, Ikon, killer21st, Whiz, YeYuwuziqi, chess, SUPERAK47, wolfzhou, yun_shou, kawamura, yaya, johncid, eggttball.
monkey games means 1 vs N  ( N >= 2 )   ,right?
Yes Tornado. Another property of these games that there is one "master game" and other games are "replica"

So the progress of games looks:
Eg. on "master" board move 31. played
Few hours or days break?
On "replica" borad move 31. also played    etc
Few players prefer using this tactics. There is no problem with it because all boards are public (no hidden boards)
What is the advantage of this tactics? Please answer!
if i have a win, then i get two points
1. Copying of stronger player moves good idea for beginner: learning the theory and time sparing. The "copier" has more time to analyze critical games.
yes, you sayd it more clear
copying is good only for the current tournament
But, It has a drawback: if the stronger player plays poorly!
or if next time someone plays a different move, the copier has not understood the previous moevs, and so won't be prepared for a surprise

Another advantage is:
2. Set up identical openings on some borads and playing exactly same games getting same results: wins or draws. Here you need to know the theory very well. It is also time saving method.
but the question is whether the copier could understand the theory of stronger player.
there could be also advantage for team playing
for copying to be efficient, one must at one point anyway analyse, why such moves were played
Yes, this tactics risky for beginner, but otherways also lose with simple way...
Second advantage was for advanced players.
for example we are a team, all open d3, but one knows better 15-L10, other knows 15-j11, so depends on opponent's moves, one of us continue and we all win
Yes, you need to know theory the very well. Agree?
But, It has also a drawback: if you get same results like many LOSES :-)
Becuse of your opponents can "share" analysis time. It means, if one of your opponents find a good move then rest of your opponents simply copy this move :-)
so ,it seems that the result depends on the strongest player of each side.  :)
A little mistake in analysis result in big deficit! Getting same loses in same time!
that is why ppl do not make rule to stop this practice?
how could you make such a rule ? how do you prove, that someone is only copying? :)
It is hard to create good rule about it, maybe best way to create hidden boards
only players and admins can watch on?
as making some small offices for every 2 players
But with hidden board, you cannot avoid about "team work".
Yes only two players can see that board
have your own idea is so help for you,in your games
The topic is "monkey games" in offline tournaments
On the contrary, if you know somewhere a new theory line or tricky position then you can trap more opponents same time!!!
It is risky, but without calculated risk you cannot gain good result!
So without risk, you can gain about average result
After this introduction, let's see examples. Are you ready?
Here mcmanus played 7 games: 5 games with black color. His starategy was here to gain at least 3.5 points.
His plan was not successful because of he realized only 2.5 points.
And he had fortune with this 2.5 points
If his opponent more hungry, then he can get only 1.5 points.

With white, here he made theory mistake and Renju_Liu_t said "thank you very much". It is black sure win. If this game maybe draw then Renju_liu_t and me have same points, then Berger coefficient would decide.
Everybody can analyse it at home
Another mcmanus's game with white stones was draw against Aurora.
This is the main theory line. All moves are forced.
What do you think about this position? Is it black win? Is it draw? Or is it white win?
It is not obvious that it is sure draw. I have not seen any proof about yet.
I can say only that BLACK CAN FORCE DRAW, but black has long and strong tempo.
On contrary, if somewhere any player makes a little mistake then opponent can win.
In this theory line mcmanus played 4 identical game with black stones.
I am GLAD I was not at final tournament :) I hate this position! :)
He thought, he would get here 4 half points!
What do you think, is it draw line or not? Please answer!
black certainly do not try to win ...
Yes in this line: black can fill up the board and upper are will make a good defensive move

There were 4 identical same game here:  mcmanus-voshkod
mcmanus-Renju_YinLC
mcmanus-virag
mcmanus-Padovan
What do you think now, is it draw line or not? Please answer!
I think white can attack a bit
Many students said draw, abot 95 %, but I think all students agree that white has a tempo now
yes, and quite long line of attack too
There was a big delay here, and finally voshkod and Renju_YinLC were impatient and they realized that only chance to win here by time.
They played absolutly same sequence from move 68 up to 104.
The move 68. d2 is very questionable. Why?
If lower side black had a threat, then move 65 is unimportant.
black can not win there, anyhow
66 is understandable move yet, becuse of it was copied from board mcmanus-Padovan
66 is good move for White to win at Upper Right side.
of course 66 is good, but followed by 68 - k2 makes no sense
upright corner is the only chance for white
but it is very hard to win.
Yes, I am happy that all studenst understand the position
Games mcmanus-voshkod and mcmanus-Renju_YinLC ended as draw finally.
I think b10 is good for white
so both voshkod and Renju_LC both played this 68th?
and both played same sequence from 68 to 104 :-)
copying with no meaning at all. ?
My move was here this 68. K12
Mcmanus realized here that black is in big trouble.
So he changed his tactics, he paused this game, that voshkod and Renju_YinLC was not able to copy white victory sequence from this board.
So he let this game in run out of time without moving.
"Run out of time" equals RESIGN BUTTON :-)
yes, but he did not lose another 2 games
is it white win here after 69 - j13?
Yes, It was a good tactics/strategy decision from mcmanus, it earns for him two half points.
Fermat mentioned this board in renjuClass forum
He did not understand why mcmanus let it run out of time
Do you know good black defence here?
N9 also possible, but not too good defence
Yes, simple L12, but hard to define what is the "simple" renju move :-)
What do you think, what is the possible black defence here?
Who would like to show white win here?
So we can conclude this 71 not so good defence.
This also not good, here white has a VCF. Evrybody can see VCF line?
What is the next white move?
please everybody give some advice for white
k13, and the after the only black defence e12
black can defens also g13, h11, after k13
black must block k13 with fours and play 77-L14, then white e12 :)
not direct win, white fear about black VCF line, but that line is absolutly fake
what is the risk of K13?
This is the most direct win
black must play fours and 77 L14
If you understand the position, it is most simplest way
Let's see who to defend black here
Threaten overline at L column and 4x4 threat at H11, so black need to eliminate 4x4 threat first.
No black VCF becuse of cut!
And now. We got a 3 kyu renju problem in the upper right corner :-)
Black can use his unusable fours on the chance of winning by time.
VCT sequence started at move 66 and ended at move 105. It is 39 move deep victory line.
You can lengthen it to 46 move deep line :-)
On pbm, if black has another 4-5 four threat then game is draw becuse of after 120 moves, the game is declared as draw :-)
Any other back defences very poor
I think in offline tournaments point system should be changed
so that draw is 1 point, where as win is 3 points
but this position wouldn't be so played, if winning was made more rewarding
but now white has a sequence with 3x3 on e13
In conclusion, I think it was good example for you, that you need to be very careful about "monkey games" :)
Thank you for your attention! Now the lesson is over!
not to play them with virag :)
